### Base URLs

@auth = http://127.0.0.1:4000
@user = http://localhost:3000

---

### 1. Health Check

GET {{user}}/health

---

### 2. Login → Get JWT Token

POST {{auth}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser"
}

---

### 3. Save token manually from above response

# Replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE with actual token returned from login
---
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyIjoidGVzdHVzZXIiLCJpYXQiOjE3Nzc3ODU2NzAsImV4cCI6MTc3Nzc4OTI3MH0.IIKI_0qfENcrO-8RvzWZ7793rr0i4oEbd5ySSiSlFxE

---

### 4. Get All Users (Authorized)

GET {{user}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 5. Get User by ID (Authorized)

GET {{user}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 6. Create User (Authorized)

POST {{user}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com"
}

---

### 7. Unauthorized Request (No Token)

GET {{user}}/api/users

---

### 8. Invalid Token Test

GET {{user}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer invalidtoken